commentPostTextItems.html: It was clear from the moment that West Indies lost four early wickets that they would have a lot of catching up to do. Smith and Bernard put up some resistance but the delay in taking the batting Powerplay seems to have cost the team dear. Bangladesh notch up their first ODI win over West Indies and lead the the three match series 1-0
Join us in a while for presentations

Abdul Razzak gets the Man of the match award for his four wicket haul and he says that he is not surprised at taking the new ball and says he had experience in 2007 WC. He adds that it feels nice to perform well on his return back to the team
